Source: aptura-secureboot
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Aptura <packages@aptura.example>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: aptura-secureboot
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 sbsigntool,
 mokutil,
 openssl,
 efibootmgr
Description: Aptura OS Secure Boot key management
 Lets the custom (unsigned-by-upstream) Aptura kernel boot with Secure Boot
 enabled. Generates a per-machine Machine Owner Key on first boot, signs every
 installed Aptura kernel with it (also on kernel updates), and guides the user
 through the one-time firmware enrollment. The private key never leaves the
 machine and is not part of the image.
